Studies of functional connectivity in ADHD are rapidly evolving. Two general approaches have been taken: task-based and resting state. Task-based
methods generally examine group differences in correlation strength between regions with a seed-based approach or through a psycho-physiological
interaction (PPI) analysis, a method for quantifying correlated activity between two brain areas and its modulation by task context. Datasets in the table
