Studies of the brain at rest have taken a number of different approaches, including independent components analysis (ICA), small-world network analysis
(measuring network inclusiveness of nodes and efﬁciency of the network as a whole), graph theory approaches (quantifying correlated activity between sets
of ROIs simultaneously), and the aforementioned seed-based approach. Datasets consisted of all male subjects unless otherwise noted by percentage in
brackets. All studies used functional magnetic resonance imaging.
ACC, anterior cingulate cortex; dACC, dorsal anterior cingulate cortex; DMN, default mode network; IFG, inferior frontal gyrus; MFG, middle frontal gyrus;
OFC, orbitofrontal cortex; PCC, posterior cingulate cortex; PFC, prefrontal cortex; PreC, precuneus; SB, seed-based; STG, superior temporal gyrus; vmPFC,
ventromedial prefrontal cortex.
