regional homogeneity (see following) and the standard variance of its low-frequency ﬂuctuations.
cDataset is same as in Castellanos et al. (39).
dRegional homogeneity is a novel measure, unique to this study in the ADHD literature, assessing temporal synchrony of the regional blood oxygen level
dependent signal.
eALFF refers to amplitude of low-frequency ﬂuctuations ( .08 Hz) and might be suggestive of local spontaneous neuronal activity.
